						<summary>

						<p>Slab at the doorway in front of the Vīrabhadra temple.</p>						

						<p>This is dated in the cyclic year <hi rend="bold">Vikāri, Pushya, ba. 3.</hi> On the basis of palaeography, it may be assigned to the 16th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>It refers to an <hi rend="italic">edurugaḍa</hi> executed by Yeṟṟabhaṭlu Mallubhaṭlu in favour of Taṁbaḷa Jakkaya cancelling the original bond lost by the former, as the loan of half a <hi rend="italic">Varāha</hi> advance by him had been fully paid by the latter.</p>						

						</summary>
